DOM
Document Object Model - is programing interface for HTML and XLM documents
DOM - is interface for handling an interface
DOM is used to manipulate the page in various ways:

    Searching for elements
    Changing element content
    Changing HTML structure of the page
    Changing CSS styling of the page

DOM is called Object Model for it presents the page as an object, containing an object representing each element within it
DOM not dependent of any programming languages.
Element and its Locator:
WebElement - is an object representing HTML element on the page
WebElement locator aka selector - is a query that finds and returns specific elements from the DOM

child elements are located under dozens of layers
